FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - MONGOLIA (03): (OVORHANGAY, DUNDGOVI) SHEEP, GOAT, SEROTYPE O, OIE
*****************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 8 Sep 2021
Source: OIE WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2021 [edited]
https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=39221


Foot-and-mouth disease virus, Mongolia
--------------------------------------
General information
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 6 Aug 2021
Confirmed: 9 Aug 2021
Reported: 7 Sep 2021
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 27 Jul 2021
Causal agent: foot-and-mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a determined zone of the country.

Outbreak location 1: Bayangol soum, Ovorhangay
Date of start of the outbreak: 7 Aug 2021
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Sheep/goats (mixed herd) / 423 / 5 / - / - / - / 423

Outbreak location 2: Erdenedalai soum, Dundgovi
Date of start of the outbreak: 6 Aug 2021
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Sheep/goats (mixed herd) / - / 70 / - / - / - / 824

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: illegal movement of animals, animals in transit, contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering points

Epidemiological comments: illegal livestock movement

Control measures at event level
Domestic control measures applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s), quarantine, disinfection

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: State Central Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory)
Species / Outbreaks / Test / Tested from / Result
Sheep/goats (mixed herd) / 2 / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 9 Aug 2021 / positive
Sheep/goats (mixed herd) / 1 / ELISA for the detection of antibodies against non-structural proteins (NSP ELISA) / 7 Aug 2021 / positive

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

